<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Works_cited">Works cited</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Town_meeting&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Works cited"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><cite id="CITEREFMansbridge1980" class="citation book cs1">Mansbridge, Jane J. (1980). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/beyondadversaryd00mansrich"><i>Beyond Adversary Democracy</i></a></span>. New York: Basic Books. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780465006571" title="Special:BookSources/9780465006571"><bdi>9780465006571</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Beyond+Adversary+Democracy&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Basic+Books&amp;rft.date=1980&amp;rft.isbn=9780465006571&amp;rft.aulast=Mansbridge&amp;rft.aufirst=Jane+J.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fbeyondadversaryd00mansrich&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATown+meeting" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFLockridge1985" class="citation book cs1">Lockridge, Kenneth (1985). <span class="id-lock-registration" title="Free registration required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/newenglandtown00lock"><i>A New England Town</i></a></span>. New York: W.W. Norton &amp; Company. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-393-95459-3" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-393-95459-3"><bdi>978-0-393-95459-3</bdi></a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+New+England+Town&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=W.W.+Norton+%26+Company&amp;rft.date=1985&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-393-95459-3&amp;rft.aulast=Lockridge&amp;rft.aufirst=Kenneth&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fnewenglandtown00lock&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATown+meeting" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Town_meeting&amp;action=edit&amp;section=28" title="Edit section: Further reading"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li>Bryan, Frank M., <i>Real Democracy: The New England Town Meeting and How it Works</i>, Chicago and London: University of Chicago Press, 2004.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFFiske1904" class="citation book cs1">Fiske, John (1904). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/civilgovernment00sanfgoog"><i>Civil Government in the United States: Considered with Some Reference to Its Origins</i></a>. Houghton, Mifflin Company.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Civil+Government+in+the+United+States%3A+Considered+with+Some+Reference+to+Its+Origins&amp;rft.pub=Houghton%2C+Mifflin+Company&amp;rft.date=1904&amp;rft.aulast=Fiske&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fcivilgovernment00sanfgoog&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATown+meeting" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li>Gould, John, <i>New England Town Meeting: Safeguard of Democracy</i>, Brattleboro, VT: Stephen Daye Press, 1940.</li>
<li>Mansbridge, Jane, <i>Beyond Adversary Democracy</i>, Chicago and London: University of Chicago Press, 1980, provides an in-depth account of the dynamics in one Vermont town of about 500 people.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFPorter1922" class="citation book cs1">Porter, Kirk Harold (1922). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/cu31924073969523"><i>County and Township Government in the United States</i></a>. Macmillan.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=County+and+Township+Government+in+the+United+States&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft.date=1922&amp;rft.aulast=Porter&amp;rft.aufirst=Kirk+Harold&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fcu31924073969523&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATown+meeting" class="Z3988"></span></li>
<li>Robinson, Donald. <i>Town Meeting: Practicing Democracy in Rural New England</i> (University of Massachusetts Press; 2011) 344 pages; analyzes the rocky but productive process of town-meeting democracy in Ashfield, Mass., a community of just under 2,000 in the Berkshires.</li>
<li>Zuckerman, Michael. "The Social Context of Democracy in Massachusetts," <i>William and Mary Quarterly</i>  (1968) 25:523-544  <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/1916797">in JSTOR</a></li>
<li>Town meeting time: A handbook of parliamentary law (<a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0971167907" title="Special:BookSources/0971167907">0971167907</a>)</li></ul>
